In this article, President Barack Obama delegates authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $45 million in defense articles and services of the Department of Defense, as well as military education and training. This assistance is intended to support the efforts of Benin, Cameroon, Chad, Niger, and Nigeria in their fight against the extremist group Boko Haram. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to carry out this drawdown. The memorandum concludes by instructing the publication of this delegation of authority in the Federal Register.